        <section address="ReleaseNotes">
            <title>Release notes</title>
            <content>
            </content>
            <sections>
                <section address="Terrain">
                    <title>Terrain rendering</title>
                    <content>
                        <para>
                            DigitalRise Graphics now includes support for large-scale, tile-based terrains
                            using height fields. The terrain system is designed to cover anything from
                            small game worlds up to large terrain databases.
                        </para>
                        <mediaLink>
                            <caption placement="after">
                                Figure 1: Terrain sample consisting of 2 x 2 tiles with 1024 m x 1024 m each
                            </caption>
                            <image xlink:href="Terrain"/>
                        </mediaLink>
                        <para>
                            Features:
                        </para>
                        <list class="bullet">
                            <listItem>
                                Continuous level of detail (no mesh preprocessing, no hardware tessellation required)
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                Materials using diffuse maps, specular maps, normal maps, height maps
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                Customizable effects (including parallax occlusion mapping)
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                Flexible material blending (blend maps, height-based, slope-based, etc.) using any number of layers
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                Collision detection
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                Decal rendering
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                Roads
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                Procedural terrains
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                Holes
                            </listItem>
                        </list>
                        <mediaLink>
                            <caption placement="after">
                                Figure 2: Blood decal on terrain
                            </caption>
                            <image xlink:href="Terrain-Decal"/>
                        </mediaLink>
                        <mediaLink>
                            <caption placement="after">
                                Figure 3: Road carved into terrain
                            </caption>
                            <image xlink:href="Terrain-Road"/>
                        </mediaLink>
                        <para>
                            For more details, check out the new terrain samples and the <link xlink:href="46f261f5-750c-4df5-99e2-b6a289f15098" />
                            chapter.
                        </para>
                    </content>
                </section>

                <section address="UWP">
                    <title>Windows 10: Universal Windows Platform</title>
                    <content>
                        <para>
                            This release adds builds and samples for the Universal Windows Platform (UWP).
                        </para>
                    </content>
                </section>

                <section address="Unity">
                    <title>Unity game engine</title>
                    <content>
                        <para>
                            The license requirements for the Unity game engine have been relaxed: Previously, a
                            DigitalRise Engine Professional license was required to use the DigitalRise libraries
                            in Unity. From now on Indie and Professional licenses work with Unity. (If you own
                            a DigitalRise Indie license: You can use your existing DigitalRise license key in
                            the Unity project.)
                        </para>
                    </content>
                </section>

                <section address="DRMDL">
                    <title>Importing DRMDL files</title>
                    <content>
                        <para>
                            When importing a model for use in the DigitalRise Engine, two files are required:
                            The model (e.g. the FBX file) and the model description (the DRMDL file). The model
                            description is an XML file that contains preprocessing settings and references the
                            material to be used.
                        </para>
                        <para>
                            To import the model, the FBX file needs to be added to an XNA or MonoGame content project.
                            Due to certain limitations in the XNA content pipeline it was not possible to add the
                            .drmdl file directly to the content project. This has been solved in the new release:
                            Instead of adding the FBX file to the content project, it is now possible to directly
                            add the DRMDL file to the content project.
                        </para>
                        <para>
                            This seemingly minor change solves a long standing problem with the XNA content pipeline:
                            To import a model multiple times, the model had to be duplicated on disk. Now, multiple
                            DRMDL files can reference the same model. The model can be imported/processed multiple
                            times with different settings.
                        </para>
                    </content>
                </section>
            </sections>
        </section>


        <section address="ChangeLog">
            <title>Change log</title>
            <content>
            </content>
            <sections>
                <section address="General">
                    <title>General</title>
                    <content>
                        <list class="bullet">
                            <listItem>
                                NEW: Builds for Window 10 - Universal Windows Platform (UWP).
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                NEW: Microsoft.Practices.ServiceLocation.dll updated from version 1.2 to 1.3.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                NEW: DigitalRise libraries built for Unity game engine can now be used with Indie licenses. (Previously a Professional license was required.)
                            </listItem>
                        </list>
                    </content>
                </section>
                <section address="Base">
                    <title>DigitalRise Base 1.18</title>
                    <content>
                        <list class="bullet">
                            <listItem>
                                NEW:
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">T:DigitalRise.Collections.NamedObjectCollection`1</codeEntityReference>
                                now raises
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">E:DigitalRise.Collections.NamedObjectCollection`1.CollectionChanged</codeEntityReference>
                                events.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                NEW: Methods
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false" autoUpgrade="true">M:DigitalRise.Collections.NamedObjectCollection`1.InsertRange(System.Int32,System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerable{`0})</codeEntityReference>
                                and
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false" autoUpgrade="true">M:DigitalRise.Collections.NamedObjectCollection`1.RemoveRange(System.Int32,System.Int32)</codeEntityReference>
                                added to
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">T:DigitalRise.Collections.NamedObjectCollection`1</codeEntityReference>
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                FIX:
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true" autoUpgrade="true">M:DigitalRise.Collections.NotifyingCollection`1.RemoveItem(System.Int32)</codeEntityReference>
                                is not called when calling
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false" autoUpgrade="true">M:DigitalRise.Collections.NotifyingCollection`1.RemoveRange(System.Int32,System.Int32)</codeEntityReference>.
                            </listItem>
                        </list>
                    </content>
                </section>
                <section address="Mathematics">
                    <title>DigitalRise Mathematics 1.13.1</title>
                    <content>
                        <list class="bullet">
                            <listItem>
                                CHANGE: Minor performance improvements.
                            </listItem>
                        </list>
                    </content>
                </section>
                <section address="Geometry">
                    <title>DigitalRise Geometry 1.18</title>
                    <content>
                        <list class="bullet">
                            <listItem>
                                <para>
                                    NEW:
                                    <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">T:DigitalRise.Geometry.Shapes.HeightField</codeEntityReference>
                                    now uses a 1-dimensional array. See new height field properties:
                                    <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">P:DigitalRise.Geometry.Shapes.HeightField.Samples</codeEntityReference>,
                                    <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">P:DigitalRise.Geometry.Shapes.HeightField.NumberOfSamplesX</codeEntityReference>,
                                    <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">P:DigitalRise.Geometry.Shapes.HeightField.NumberOfSamplesZ</codeEntityReference>.
                                </para>
                                <para>
                                    <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">P:DigitalRise.Geometry.Shapes.HeightField.Array</codeEntityReference>
                                    (<codeInline>float[,]</codeInline>) is obsolete. Instead, the height field data should
                                    be set using a 1-dimensional array.
                                    Please note: The property
                                    <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">P:DigitalRise.Geometry.Shapes.HeightField.Array</codeEntityReference>
                                    can still be used - but don't forget to call
                                    <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false" autoUpgrade="true">M:DigitalRise.Geometry.Shapes.HeightField.Invalidate</codeEntityReference>
                                    if the data in
                                    <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">P:DigitalRise.Geometry.Shapes.HeightField.Array</codeEntityReference>
                                    is changed after the
                                    <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">T:DigitalRise.Geometry.Shapes.HeightField</codeEntityReference>
                                    was created.
                                </para>
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                NEW:
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">T:DigitalRise.Geometry.Shapes.HeightField</codeEntityReference>
                                can have a local origin (see
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">P:DigitalRise.Geometry.Shapes.HeightField.OriginX</codeEntityReference>,
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">P:DigitalRise.Geometry.Shapes.HeightField.OriginZ</codeEntityReference>).
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                NEW: Support for holes in height fields (using NaN values in the height array).
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                NEW:
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true" autoUpgrade="true">M:DigitalRise.Geometry.GeometryHelper.MergeDuplicatePositions(System.Collections.Generic.IList{DigitalRise.Mathematics.Algebra.Vector3F},System.Single)</codeEntityReference>
                                added.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                FIX: Cloned
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">T:DigitalRise.Geometry.Shapes.ConeShape</codeEntityReference>s
                                had correct
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">P:DigitalRise.Geometry.Shapes.ConeShape.Radius</codeEntityReference>
                                and
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">P:DigitalRise.Geometry.Shapes.ConeShape.Height</codeEntityReference>
                                but derived properties (e.g. AABB) were incorrect.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                Minor other improvements.
                            </listItem>
                        </list>
                    </content>
                </section>
                <section address="Particles">
                    <title>DigitalRise Particles 1.4.1</title>
                    <content>
                        <list class="bullet">
                            <listItem>
                                FIX: Particle systems with reference frame
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">F:DigitalRise.Particles.ParticleReferenceFrame.World</codeEntityReference>
                                should not be scaled when the particle system node has a scale.
                            </listItem>
                        </list>
                    </content>
                </section>
                <section address="Graphics">
                    <title>DigitalRise Graphics 1.0</title>
                    <content>
                        <list class="bullet">
                            <listItem>
                                NEW: Terrain rendering. See <link xlink:href="46f261f5-750c-4df5-99e2-b6a289f15098" /> for more details.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                NEW: Method overload
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false" autoUpgrade="true">M:DigitalRise.Graphics.SceneGraph.ScatteringSkyNode.GetFogColor(System.Int32,System.Single)</codeEntityReference>
                                with elevation angle parameter added.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                NEW: The tag <legacyBold>GenerateTangentFrames</legacyBold> can now be set per model, per mesh, and
                                per submesh in the model description (.drmdl file).
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                NEW: Added support for adding .drmdl files directly to content project.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                NEW: The DigitalRise model processor now runs vertex cache optimizations on the meshes - a feature previously missing in MonoGame.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                NEW: DigitalRise texture processor supports new surface formats, which have been added to
                                the MonoGame content pipeline: PVRTC1 2bpp/4bpp for iOS, ETC1 for Android
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                NEW: Property
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">P:DigitalRise.Graphics.RenderContext.Object</codeEntityReference>
                                added. (Stores current data object during rendering.)
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                NEW: Effect parameter semantics <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">F:DigitalRise.Graphics.Effects.DefaultEffectParameterSemantics.NaN</codeEntityReference>
                                and <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">F:DigitalRise.Graphics.Effects.SceneEffectParameterSemantics.LodCameraPosition</codeEntityReference>
                                added.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                NEW:
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">F:DigitalRise.Graphics.GraphicsHelper.RasterizerStateCullClockwise</codeEntityReference>,
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">F:DigitalRise.Graphics.GraphicsHelper.RasterizerStateCullCounterClockwise</codeEntityReference>,
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">F:DigitalRise.Graphics.GraphicsHelper.RasterizerStateCullNone</codeEntityReference>
                                added. Identical to built-in rasterizer states in XNA, except that
                                <legacyBold>MultiSampleAntiAliasing</legacyBold>
                                is set to false, which improves line rendering when MSAA is disabled.
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">F:DigitalRise.Graphics.GraphicsHelper.RasterizerStateWireFrame</codeEntityReference>
                                now also sets
                                <legacyBold>MultiSampleAntiAliasing</legacyBold> = false.
                                The
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">T:DigitalRise.Graphics.Rendering.DebugRenderer</codeEntityReference>
                                uses the new rasterizer states to produce cleaner lines.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                NEW: Method <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true" autoUpgrade="true">M:DigitalRise.Graphics.NoiseHelper.GetNoiseTexture(DigitalRise.Graphics.IGraphicsService,System.Int32,System.Int32)</codeEntityReference>
                                added.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                CHANGE:
                                <localUri>Forward.fx</localUri> is now more customizable. Features (diffuse texture,
                                specular texture, opacity texture, vertex colors, etc.) can be turned on or off
                                using preprocessor directives.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                CHANGE: Improved height fog rendering. If height fog was combined with distance fog and camera was
                                in a low position, the skybox could get fogged ignoring the fog distance values
                                (<codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">P:DigitalRise.Graphics.Fog.Start</codeEntityReference>,
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">P:DigitalRise.Graphics.Fog.End</codeEntityReference>).
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                CHANGE: Improved normal and tangent frame calculations.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                CHANGE: DigitalRise texture processor automatically resizes textures to power-of-two or
                                multiple-of-four, if required by the output format.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                CHANGE: Water rendering: Improved projected grid resolution when camera is near water
                                surface and looking horizontally. Minor other improvements.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                REMOVE:
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">F:DigitalRise.Graphics.RenderContextKeys.Shadow</codeEntityReference>
                                is now marked as obsolete. The current shadow map can be found in
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">P:DigitalRise.Graphics.RenderContext.Object</codeEntityReference>
                                when the shadow map is being rendered.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                FIX: Fog with high height falloff could result in no fog or NaN values caused by numerical errors.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                FIX: Bounding shape of
                                ParticleSystemNode
                                needs to ignore scale if the reference frame is
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">F:DigitalRise.Particles.ParticleReferenceFrame.World</codeEntityReference>.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                FIX: AMD DX9 graphics driver crash on Win8.1 caused by cloud layer.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                FIX: Effect parameter bindings were not created for arrays in MonoGame.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                FIX: Minor pixel artifacts at the border of last shadow cascade.
                                (Problem appears only in Direct3D 11 on NVIDIA Geforce cards.)
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                FIX: No
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">T:DigitalRise.Graphics.OceanWaves</codeEntityReference>
                                were rendered if
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">P:DigitalRise.Graphics.OceanWaves.EnableCpuQueries</codeEntityReference>
                                was false.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                Minor other improvements.
                            </listItem>
                        </list>
                    </content>
                </section>
                <section address="Game">
                    <title>DigitalRise Game 1.3</title>
                    <content>
                        <list class="bullet">
                            <listItem>
                                NEW:
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">T:DigitalRise.Game.GameObjectCollection</codeEntityReference>
                                now raises
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="false">E:DigitalRise.Collections.NamedObjectCollection`1.CollectionChanged</codeEntityReference>
                                events.
                            </listItem>
                        </list>
                    </content>
                </section>
                <section address="GameUI">
                    <title>DigitalRise Game UI 1.6.1</title>
                    <content>
                        <list class="bullet">
                            <listItem>
                                FIX: Auto-generated key map contained wrong characters for Portuguese (and maybe other) keyboard layouts.
                            </listItem>
                        </list>
                    </content>
                </section>
                <section address="Samples">
                    <title>Samples</title>
                    <content>
                        <list class="bullet">
                            <listItem>
                                NEW: Windows 10 samples.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                NEW: Terrain samples (see graphics samples).
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                NEW: CustomCommandSample added (see Game UI samples.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                NEW: Added more properties to <legacyBold>FogObject</legacyBold>:
                                <legacyBold>ApplyFogToSky</legacyBold>, <legacyBold>AttachToCamera</legacyBold>
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                NEW: Added fog properties to <legacyBold>DynamicSkyObject</legacyBold>.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                CHANGE: When a model is used multiple times, the DRMDL files are added to the content
                                project instead of the FBX file. The DRMDL files reference the same FBX file,
                                which reduces the required disk space.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                CHANGE: Changed slider ranges in <legacyBold>FogObject</legacyBold> GUI.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                CHANGE: Removed use of obsolete property
                                <codeEntityReference qualifyHint="true">P:DigitalRise.Geometry.Shapes.HeightField.Array</codeEntityReference>.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                FIX: Minor fixes in parallax occlusion mapping sample.
                                Light direction tangent was not normalized. Mip level checks must use
                                &lt; instead of &lt;=
                            </listItem>
                        </list>
                    </content>
                </section>
                <section address="MonoGame">
                    <title>MonoGame</title>
                    <content>
                        <list class="bullet">
                            <listItem>
                                CHANGE: Retarget MonoGame Windows 8 project from Windows 8.0 to Windows 8.1.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                FIX: <legacyBold>VertexStride</legacyBold> was not set in
                                <legacyBold>VertexContent</legacyBold>
                                if a model contains only a position vertex channel.
                            </listItem>
                            <listItem>
                                FIX: Mesh tangent space was not computed correctly.
                            </listItem>
                        </list>
                    </content>
                </section>
            </sections>
        </section>


